data.title: Watch Comedians in Cars Getting Coffee
data.meta_description: Jerry Seinfeld's roving talk show combines coffee, laughs and vintage cars into quirky, caffeine-fueled adventures with the sharpest minds in comedy. Watch trailers & learn more.
data.text:
Jim Carrey: We Love Breathing What You're Burning, Baby

17m

Tooling around with Jerry in a blue '76 Lamborghini Countach, Jim Carrey pays tribute to his comedy idols and shows off his new passion: painting.

Jimmy Fallon: The Unsinkable Legend - Part 1

12m

Jerry picks up the irrepressible Jimmy Fallon in a jaunty '56 Corvette convertible and surprises him with a trip out on the water.

Jimmy Fallon: The Unsinkable Legend - Part 2

18m

Fresh off his boating adventure, Jimmy talks "SNL" and landing the "Tonight Show" gig. Jerry gets some unsolicited driving advice from strangers.

Alec Baldwin: Just A Lazy Shiftless Bastard

14m

Navigating the New York City streets in a 1970 Mercedes 280 SL, Jerry and Alec Baldwin swap tales of old Hollywood, open mic nights and more.

Stephen Colbert: Cut Up And Bloody But Good Looking

17m

Jerry and late-night maestro Stephen Colbert riff on masculinity and music over breakfast and take turns at the wheel of a 1964 Morgan Plus 4.

Sarah Jessica Parker: A Little Hyper-aware

20m

Jerry ventures way out of his comfort zone in a wood-paneled '76 Ford station wagon -- a car that has a special place in Sarah Jessica Parker's heart.

Trevor Noah: That's The Whole Point Of Apartheid, Jerry

21m

"The Daily Show" host Trevor Noah schools Jerry on South African history, football and more as they head to Brooklyn in an '85 Ferrari 308 GTB.

Kristen Wiig: The Volvo-ness

18m

Jerry wows the multitalented (and part-Scandinavian) Kristen Wiig with a 1964 Volvo Amazon and a trip back in time to LA's iconic House of Pies.

John Oliver: What Kind Of Human Animal Would Do This?

18m

Jerry hits a British trifecta as he picks up "Last Week Tonight" host John Oliver in a cute but impractical 1959 Triumph TR3A on a drizzly day.

Chris Rock: Kids Need Bullying

16m

For his outing with Chris Rock, Jerry chooses one of the sleekest cars ever designed: a 1969 Lamborghini Miura. But its speed gets him in trouble.

Christoph Waltz: Champagne, Cigars And Pancake Batter

14m

Rolling up in a 1957 BMW 507 roadster, Jerry whisks "Inglourious Basterds" star Christoph Waltz off for an international feast -- IHOP-style.

Tina Fey: Feces Are My Purview

17m

Tina Fey samples her first Cronut and talks about life after "30 Rock" as she and Jerry travel up and down Manhattan in a red 1967 Volvo 1800S.

Aziz Ansari: It's Like Pushing A Building Off A Cliff

17m

Jerry jumps at the chance to drive Aziz Ansari's souped-up Prevost tour bus to a roadside diner, where the two get to try out an even bigger rig.

Ricky Gervais: Madman In A Death Machine

14m

A gleeful Jerry torments Ricky Gervais with a hair-raising, high-speed drive to an island in the Bronx in a 1967 Austin-Healey 3000.

Seth Meyers: Really?!

15m

Seth Meyers looks back on his long "SNL" career and shares his dad's comedy tips as he joins Jerry for a coffee run in a 1973 Porsche 911 Carrera RS.

Norm Macdonald: A Rusty Car In The Rain

22m

Norm MacDonald crams into Jerry’s tiny (and slightly rusty) 1958 Porsche Speedster on a rainy day to talk bad gigs, clean comedy and old sitcoms.

Michael Richards: It's Bubbly Time, Jerry

18m

Michael Richards slips back into the role of Jerry's sidekick in a rickety 1962 Volkswagen Bus that takes them to a place of surprising honesty.

J.B. Smoove: Everybody Respects a Bloody Nose

15m

J.B. Smoove bonds with Jerry over zombies, bow ties and being your own biggest fan in Smoove’s all-time favorite car -- a 1964 Studebaker Avanti.

Joel Hodgson: A Taste Of Hell From On High

12m

Jerry questions ketchup bottle design and movie humor with "Mystery Science Theater 3000" creator Joel Hodgson in a 1963 Volkswagen Karmann Ghia.

Ali Wentworth: I'm Going To Take A Percocet And Let That One Go

18m

Riding high in a low-grille 1970 Mercedes Cabriolet, Ali Wentworth schools Jerry on the finer points of WASP etiquette and the art of winning a fight.

Barack Obama: Just Tell Him You Are The President

19m

Jerry pulls up in a 1963 Corvette Stingray to take President Barack Obama out for coffee, only to wind up making his own in a White House break room.

Kevin Hart: You Look Amazing In The Wind

20m

Kevin Hart joins Jerry for a "weird male date" in a diminutive 1959 Porsche RSK Spyder, shopping for sneakers, sipping green smoothies and more.

Will Ferrell: Mr. Ferrell, For The Last Time, We're Going To Ask You To Put The Cigar Out

18m

A cartoon-inspired 1970 Plymouth Road Runner Superbird takes Jerry and Will Ferrell to a beachside café with a big menu and delicious baklava.

Howard Stern: The Last Days Of Howard Stern

14m

Jerry drags Howard Stern to a Queens diner in a 1969 Pontiac GTO dubbed "The Judge" for a spirited debate about self-esteem and therapy.

Mel Brooks & Carl Reiner: I Want Sandwiches, I Want Chicken

17m

After a drive with Carl Reiner in a 1960 Rolls Royce, Jerry takes a 1970 Porsche 911S to Reiner's home to have dinner with comedy icon Mel Brooks.

Julia Louis-Dreyfus: I'll Go If I Don't Have To Talk

17m

Jerry takes Julia Louis-Dreyfus for a drive down memory lane in a 1964 Aston Martin DB5, cracking up over lukewarm cappuccinos just like old times.

Don Rickles: You'll Never Play The Copa

15m

Don Rickles joins Jerry for a ride in a 1958 Cadillac Eldorado to talk baseball, comedy and working in Vegas at Factor's Famous Deli.

Judd Apatow: Escape from Syosset

16m

Judd Apatow and Jerry hop into a 1968 Firebird 400 convertible to swap stories about Garry Shandling and stand-up over burgers and chocolate shakes.

David Letterman: I Like Kettlecorn

20m

Jerry picks up talk show legend David Letterman in Dave's own deceptively sensible 1995 Volvo station wagon -- a gift from screen icon Paul Newman.

Amy Schumer: I'm Wondering What It's Like To Date Me

16m

Jerry and Amy Schumer end up at a modest diner in the Bronx when a 1971 Ferrari Daytona 365 GTB/4 has a few mechanical issues on the road.

Steve Harvey: Always Do The Banana Joke First

18m

Jerry heads to Chicago in a 1957 Chevy Bel Air convertible, where he and local legend Steve Harvey talk about what it takes to make it in comedy.

Steve Martin: If You See This On A Toilet Seat, Don't Sit Down

24m

Steve Martin joins Jerry for a ride to Westchester County in a 1954 Siata 8V, and on the way they talk about Steve's classic stand-up act.

Jon Stewart: The Sound Of Virginity

18m

The good news is Jerry gets to pick up Jon Stewart in the first car Jon ever owned. The bad news is it's a 1978 AMC Gremlin. So Jerry switches it up.

Patton Oswalt: How Would You Kill Superman?

13m

Jerry and Patton Oswalt's ride in a DeLorean goes poorly, so they find an alternate way to get to a hip coffee shop in an emerging LA neighborhood.

Jay Leno: Comedy Is A Concealed Weapon

21m

Jay Leno has his first cup of coffee ever while he and Jerry reminisce about their stand-up past and ride around in a 1949 Porsche 356/2.

Jim Gaffigan: Stick Around For The Pope

19m

Jerry picks up family man Jim Gaffigan in a 1977 Volkswagen Bus and they lumber around Manhattan and eat pastrami at the 2nd Avenue Deli.

Fred Armisen: I Wasn't Told About This

18m

Fred Armisen and Jerry cruise around Portland, Oregon, in a 1965 Saab 96 Monte Carlo 850 and experience "hipster service" in the coffee-crazy city.

Garry Shandling: It's Great That Garry Shandling Is Still Alive

22m

In a 1979 Porsche 911 Turbo, Jerry and Garry Shandling head to LA's Comedy Store to share old stories and reflect on comics who have passed on.

Cedric The Entertainer: Dictators, Comics, And Preachers

15m

Cedric the Entertainer joins Jerry in a 1958 Bentley S1, and they discuss the "pre-laugh," the survival mindset of comedians and more.

Margaret Cho: You Can Go Cho Again

18m

Margaret Cho and Jerry head to LA's Highland Cafe in a 1967 Mazda Cosmo Sport, then Jerry helps Margaret make amends for a stand-up set gone wrong.

Lorne Michaels: Everybody Likes To See The Monkeys

16m

Jerry takes "Saturday Night Live" creator Lorne Michaels on a ride in a 1955 Mercedes 300 SL Gullwing and they talk about the history of the show.

Brian Regan: A Monkey And A Lava Lamp

15m

In a 1970 Dodge Challenger T/A, Jerry and Brian Regan head for Santa Monica to grab some coffee and riff on a variety of topics.

Robert Klein: Opera Pimp

16m

Jerry heads up to Westchester County in a 1967 Jaguar Mark 2 to meet up with stand-up icon Robert Klein and discuss other comedy legends.

Todd Barry: So You're Mellow And Tense?

15m

Todd Barry takes his first ever ride in a sports car when Jerry picks him up in a 1966 MGB Roadster and they head off to Nathan's in Coney Island.

Ted L. Nancy: You Don't Want To Offend A Cannibal

9m

In a 1966 Porsche 356 SC Cabriolet once used as a Dutch police car, Jerry and Barry Marder (aka Ted L. Nancy) head to the Bendix Diner in New Jersey.

Bill Maher: The Comedy Team Of Smug And Arrogant

19m

In a 1979 VW Bug police car, Jerry and longtime friend Bill Maher cruise around LA and discuss their beginnings in comedy, politics, music and more.

Sarah Silverman: I'm Going To Change Your Life Forever

19m

Sarah Silverman talks to Jerry about her family, religion, the hygiene of comics and more as they drive around in a 1969 Jaguar E-Type Series 2.

Bill Burr: Smoking Past The Band

18m

Jerry and self-professed "Ford guy" Bill Burr take a ride to Santa Monica in a red 1970 Mustang Boss 302 and discuss the underlying anger in comedy.

Gad Elmaleh: No Lipsticks For Nuns

18m

Jerry picks up a French comic in a French car as Gad Elmaleh joins him in a 1950 Citroën 2CV for a jaunt around New York City.

Colleen Ballinger: Happy Thanksgiving Miranda

21m

Jerry hits the road in a 1960 Austin-Healey Sprite, and takes the chronically annoyed Miranda Sings to an LA diner for some Thanksgiving food.

Larry David: Larry Eats A Pancake

16m

Jerry and old pal Larry David take a 1952 VW Bug for a spin and discuss their lazy working relationship, Larry's unusual eating habits and more.

Sebastian Maniscalco: I Don't Think That's Bestiality

16m

In a classic 1969 Camaro Z28, Jerry and Sebastian Maniscalco talk about overly casual environments, Sebastian’s mean resting face and more.

Lewis Black: At What Point Am I Out From Under?

16m

Jerry picks up eternally exasperated Lewis Black in an appropriately black Cadillac Eldorado for a drive to the legendary Junior's in Brooklyn.

Colin Quinn & Mario Joyner: I Hear Downton Abbey Is Pretty Good...

12m

Colin Quinn joins Jerry for a ride to Brooklyn in a 1976 Triumph TR6, where they meet up with their comedian friend Mario Joyner.

Bob Einstein: Unusable On The Internet

16m

In a 1970 Mercedes-Benz 300SEL 6.3, Jerry and Bob Einstein head to a bowling alley, then hit two different delis in search of the perfect lunch.

Louis C.K.: Comedy, Sex And The Blues Numbers

23m

After a ride in a quirky 1959 Fiat Jolly, Louis C.K. takes Jerry out on his boat and recounts the time he ran aground with his daughters aboard.

Kathleen Madigan: Stroked Out On A Hot Machine

18m

Jerry drives a 1972 BMW 2002 to pick up Kathleen Madigan and Chuck Martin, and they discuss the different worlds of stand-up and TV comedy.

George Wallace: Two Polish Airline Pilots

17m

Jerry joins his old buddy George Wallace on-stage at the Flamingo in Las Vegas, then the pair take a ride down the Strip in a 1965 Buick Riviera.

Bob Einstein: It's Not So Funny When It's Your Mother

23m

When he finally gets his 2017 Acura NSX, Jerry decides he wants to present it as a gift to Bob Einstein ... if this episode of the show goes well.

Zach Galifianakis: From The Third Reich To You

23m

Zach Galifianakis joins Jerry for bike shopping and doughnuts in a Volkswagen Thing before turning the tables and making Jerry sit between two ferns.

Dave Chappelle: Nobody Says, “I Wish I Had A Camera”

17m

In Washington, D.C., Jerry and Dave Chappelle take a ride in a 1973 Citroën Maserati SM and pay a visit to Dave's old high school.

Ellen DeGeneres: You Said It Wasn’t Funny

18m

Jerry picks up Ellen DeGeneres in a 1977 Toyota FJ40 Land Cruiser. They discuss her start in comedy, then Ellen teaches Jerry a lesson about car keys.

Tracy Morgan: Lasagna With Six Different Cheeses

17m

In a 1984 Ferrari 288 GTO, Jerry and Tracy Morgan do some grocery shopping, talk about raisins and hit a diner in Ridgewood, New Jersey.

Brian Regan: Are There Left Handed Spoons?

18m

Jerry picks up Brian Regan in Brian's favorite car, a Cadillac XLR convertible, and they get coffee and visit a golf shop (to Jerry's chagrin).

Dana Carvey: Na.. Ga.. Do.. It

19m

Dana Carvey and Jerry roll in a Meyers Manx dune buggy to the Beverly Hills Hotel for coffee, then Dana plays guitar for Jerry at a music store.

Hasan Minhaj: Nobody Cries At A Joke

14m

Jerry picks up basketball enthusiast Hasan Minhaj in a 1992 Ferrari 512 TR and tries to explain why baseball's better over coffee and pancakes.

Neal Brennan: Red Bottom Shoes Equals Fantastic Babies

15m

Jerry takes Neal Brennan to Hermosa Beach in a 1965 Porsche 356C Coupe to discuss comic philosophies and why they didn't watch each other's shows.

John Mulaney: A Hooker In The Rain

18m

In a 1969 Alfa Romeo Giulia Super, Jerry and John Mulaney do some rug shopping for John's apartment and head to Staten Island for pizza and coffee.

Kate McKinnon: A Brain In A Jar

18m

Kate McKinnon joins Jerry for a jaunt around Manhattan in a 1962 Fiat 600 Multipla, and they dive into topics like the Coriolis effect over coffee.

Alec Baldwin: Gyrating, Naked Twister

21m

Jerry picks up Alec Baldwin in a 1974 BMW 3.0 CS coupe, and they drive to their shared hometown of Massapequa, New York, to swap old stories.

Ricky Gervais: China Maybe? Part 2

15m

Jerry and Ricky stop at a bakery, ponder unfunny comedians and Holocaust jokes, then try not to run out of things to say while stuck in traffic.

Matthew Broderick: These People That Do This Stuff. They Stink.

20m

In a 2018 Lamborghini Huracán, Jerry and Matthew Broderick roll by Matthew's old home, find trouble at Patagonia and live out a baseball fantasy.

Jamie Foxx: You Got To Get The Alligator Sweat

18m

Jerry takes a 1969 Maserati Mistral to New Orleans to meet Jamie Foxx. Jamie talks about his comedy inspiration and how he stays humble and hungry.

Sebastian Maniscalco: My Wife Didn't Know The Extent Of It

16m

Rolling around in vintage Italian scooters, Jerry and Sebastian Maniscalco discuss likes and dislikes and how comedians function in "normal" society.

Martin Short: A Dream World Of Residuals

19m

Martin Short talks about the '70s Toronto comedy scene and being funny on demand as he and Jerry drive around LA in a 1983 Mercedes station wagon.

Mario Joyner: He Should Have Been Done That

17m

In a 1974 VW Thing, Jerry and his old friend Mario Joyner hit up a barbershop, eat chicken and waffles, and discuss being a well-rounded entertainer.

Melissa Villaseñor

13m

Jerry and impressionist Melissa Villaseñor visit a Brooklyn food museum in a 1991 Nissan Figaro and talk funny voices and Silly Putty.

Bridget Everett: Still Hot To The Touch

16m

Cabaret performer Bridget Everett finds some pent-up anger in Jerry, and the pair get tarot readings while cruising in a 1961 Cadillac convertible.

Barry Marder: Big Lots and BevMo!

17m

Jerry picks up longtime friend Barry Marder in a 1966 Porsche 356 SC Cabriolet, and they rank bodily functions, go shopping and eat Twinkies.
